About the Episode:

It is early 1957 and the Griffin family has been blown apart since the revelation in Boston that 
Quirke is Phoebe's natural father. Quirke is drinking heavily; Mal and Sarah's marriage is on the 
rocks; Sarah is regretting the missed chances of twenty years before; Quirke and his adoptive 
father the formidable Judge Garret Griffin are estranged; and Phoebe has decided to assert her 
freedom from the lot of them by moving out of the family home.

Nothing anyone can say can dissuade her, and Quirke resolves to look out for her as best he can. 
But Phoebe pushes Quirke and the family away, defiantly taking up with a louche and dangerous 
young man by the name of Leslie White. 


I hope you enjoy.
